In [26]:
def plot_near_0(model, f, ylim, title):
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('$x$')
    plt.ylabel('$\phi$')
    plt.xlim([-0.01, 0.21])
    plt.ylim(ylim)
    plt.plot(model.xs, model.phi[-1], '-o')
    a_higher = model.df_additional.iloc[-1, -3]
    b_higher = model.df_additional.iloc[-1, -2]
    rs = np.linspace(0.00001, 0.21, 400)
    plt.plot(rs, f(a_higher, b_higher, rs))
    for i in range(5):
        x = i * model.params['dx']
        plt.plot([x, x], [-1, 1], '--', color='black')
    plt.show()

    return a * r**2 * (np.log(r) - 1) + b * r**2
